Fetch (memoised) flywire cell type information from flytable

flytable_cell_types(
  pattern = NULL,
  version = NULL,
  timestamp = NULL,
  target = c("type", "cell_type", "hemibrain_type", "cell_class"),
  transfer_hemibrain_type = c("extra", "none", "all"),
  cache = TRUE
)

Arguments

pattern

Optional character vector specifying a pattern that cell types must match in a SQL LIKE statement executed by flytable_query. The suffix _L or _R can be used to restricted to neurons annotated to the L or R hemisphere. See examples.

version

An optional CAVE materialisation version number. See details and examples.

timestamp

An optional timestamp as a string or POSIXct, interpreted as UTC when no timezone is specified.

target

A character vector specifying which flytable columns pattern should match. The special value of type means either cell_type or hemibrain_type should match.

transfer_hemibrain_type

Whether to transfer the hemibrain_type column into the cell_type (default TRUE, see details)

cache

Whether to cache the results for 5m (default TRUE since this is a little expensive)

Value

The original data.frame left joined to appropriate rows from flytable.

Details

when transfer_hemibrain_type=TRUE, hemibrain_type values will be transferred into the cell_type column if cell_type is empty.
